So proud of my mom and dad who‚Äôve been fighting the good fight since day one, which is protecting the unborn and voiceless as well as the sanctity of motherhood.  My mom volunteered for years at the Crisis Pregnancy Center helping young women in a difficult position choose to KEEP their baby. In fact, many women would show up to the Crisis Pregnancy Center thinking it was an abortion clinic just to find out otherwise. My mom would sit with these women and tell them that they were a mother now, and that they could be a mother to a dead baby or a living baby. Once a mother, always a mother. I always thought those words were very powerful. She counseled many women out of abortions and have had women thank her for her support. My mom told me she would often feel the Holy Spirit guide her on what to say to these women.  The Crisis Pregnancy Center offers women numerous resources and options that won‚Äôt harm their baby. The CPC here in Richmond Virginia would help place women into a home if they were in an abusive relationship and pregnant. The CPC even supplies women with baby bottles, blankets, strollers, and other necessities for mothers struggling financially. As you can see there‚Äôs a community waiting to help mothers caught in a crisis. I should also mention that there are far more Crisis Pregnancy Centers than there are planned parenthood clinics and that they go by another name ‚ÄúPregnancy Resource Center‚Äù My dad has been speaking out against abortion publicly since before I was born. He was even featured in The Richmond Times Dispatch covering partial birth abortions. Not only that, he‚Äôs been writing a powerful novel that shines a light on the satanic side of abortion. It‚Äôs a story about a woman who decided to fight for her baby rather than to abort her baby. This novel has tons of current political parallels as well. The novel is still in the works for now.  I‚Äôm very proud of the both of them and blessed to have grown up in a Christian household here in the great state of Virginia.
